    "recap_headline": "",
    "recap_text": "New Orleans, La. --\nCreighton Baseball took an early 2-0 lead in the opening frame, then the pitching staff made sure that was all that was needed in a 2-1 road win at Tulane on Saturday, March 14.\nThe win lifted Creighton to 7-8 on the season, while Tulane fell to 9-10 overall.\nRocco Gump\nand\nNate McHugh\ngot the Bluejays going from the jump with consecutive singles to start the game. One out later\nBen North\ngave Creighton all the offense it would need with a two-run double down the left field line.\nA quartet of Bluejay hurlers held Tulane at bay, allowing just one run on seven hits. Starter\nIan Koosman\ntook the ball into the fourth, allowing one run on four hits and four walks. Reliever\nEvan Stratton\ncame on to deliver five outs, then handed the ball over to J.T. Adams for 2.2 innings of scoreless ball. Adams allowed just one hit and one walk as he earned the win (1-1), while\nMatt Goldenbaum\ncollected his second save of the season with a hitless ninth.\nNorth and\nJoe Washburn\nled the Creighton offense with two hits, while six other Bluejays accounted for one hit each\nCreighton and Tulane meet in the series finale on Sunday at 12:00 pm."
  },
